  "market_context": "New York session on Thu 25 Apr 24; price swept prior range high (around 5100–5110), formed a bullish reversal candle (open low high close) with large lower wick, then continued higher. Daily bias was bullish (price below midnight open).",
  "key_observation": "Price swept a prior swing high (liquidity), reversed with an open-low-high-close bullish reversal candle showing change in state of delivery, and expanded upward—validating a market structure shift.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a liquidity sweep of the previous range high (BSL) just before NY session open.",
    "Step 2: Observed the formation of a bullish reversal candle (open low high close) with a large lower wick, indicating price moved down after opening but closed strongly above open.",
    "Step 3: Confirmed change in state of delivery as price closed above the series of prior down-close candles, signaling a shift to bullish delivery.",
    "Step 4: Noted the daily bias was bullish (price trading below midnight open), aligning HTF context with LTF reversal signal.",
    "Step 5: Anticipated continuation higher based on the reversal candle’s structure and alignment with NY kill zone timing."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "A liquidity sweep followed by a bullish reversal candle (OLHC) with change in state of delivery is a high-probability bullish setup—especially when aligned with daily bias and NY session timing. The wick size relative to body confirms reversal intent.",
